decks.notes: This deck aims to disrupt the opponent's game plan by playing hate cards like Archon of Emeria and Chancellor of the Annex, while also putting pressure on the opponent with aggressive creatures like White Plume Adventurer and Witch Enchanter. The deck also utilizes powerful artifacts like Black Lotus and Moxen to accelerate its mana production. By combining aggressive creatures with disruptive elements, this deck seeks to control the game and hinder the opponent's ability to execute their strategy effectively.

The main idea of this deck is to aggressively use Bazaar of Baghdad to fill the graveyard with powerful creatures like Hollow One, Vengevine, and Squee, Goblin Nabob. By utilizing free spells like Force of Will and Force of Negation, as well as disruptive cards like Wasteland and Chalice of the Void, the deck can disrupt the opponent while quickly overwhelming them with a swarm of creatures. The deck also includes card draw and graveyard recursion effects to maintain momentum and consistency in executing its game plan.

The main concept of this Merfolk aggro deck is to utilize powerful Merfolk creatures like Merrow Reejerey, Hullbreacher, and True-Name Nemesis along with disruptive spells like Force of Will and Sink into Stupor to quickly overwhelm the opponent and control the board. With efficient mana acceleration from Moxen and lands like Ancient Tomb and Cavern of Souls, along with disruptive elements like Chalice of the Void and Mental Misstep, the deck aims to establish an aggressive board presence early on and disrupt the opponent's game plan to secure a swift victory.

This deck focuses on using the card Doomsday to set up a powerful win condition by manipulating the top cards of the library. It includes fast mana accelerants like Mox Jet and Black Lotus, as well as a range of card draw and manipulation spells to find and set up the Doomsday combo. The deck also includes protection spells like Force of Will and Flusterstorm to ensure the combo is successful. The goal is to efficiently assemble the right combination of cards to win the game in a single turn.

The focus of this deck is overwhelming the opponent with aggressive artifact creatures, backed up by disruptive cards like Null Rod, Sphere of Resistance, and Thorn of Amethyst. The deck also aims to lock down the opponent's resources with cards like Wasteland and Crucible of Worlds while generating advantage with Golos, Tireless Pilgrim and Stonecoil Serpent. Karn, the Great Creator provides utility and additional threats, making it difficult for the opponent to mount a defense. Overall, the deck seeks to establish early dominance and maintain pressure throughout the game.
